# SDD Process Rules

Rationale: [01-sdd-loop.md](../../docs/workflows/01-sdd-loop.md). Engine: the `tlc-spec-driven` skill.
(Always-on rule — kept light; pull the doc on demand instead of force-loading it every turn.)

## Order

- New project → run **Discovery** first ([00-discovery.md](../../docs/workflows/00-discovery.md)).
- Every feature → `Specify → (Design) → (Tasks) → Execute → Validate`, depth auto-sized.
- Trivial change → Quick Mode (still: one-line task + verify + commit).

## Hard rules

- **Spec before code.** No non-trivial change without a spec/task carrying a traceable requirement id.
- **One task = one atomic commit** (Conventional Commits). Verify "Done when" criteria *before* committing.
- **No scope creep.** Touch only files the task names. Out-of-task ideas → `STATE.md` Deferred + roadmap parking lot.
- **Respect architecture** (`architecture.mdc`) — never break a boundary to finish faster.
- **AI changes ship with evals** (`ai-guardrails.mdc`).

## Traceability

- spec id → task → commit must form a chain. Validation checks which requirement ids are verified.

## Session hygiene

- `Pause work` before stopping (writes `HANDOFF.md`); `Resume work` to continue.
- Keep loaded context lean (target < 40k tokens); load specs/design/tasks on demand, never multiple feature specs at once.
